               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_139-item1">
                     <locus from="1">(fol. 1)</locus>
                     <author key="person_39386818">Aelred of Rievaulx</author>
                     <title key="work_265">Sermones de oneribus</title>
                     <note>Here regarded as consisting of thirty-one sermons, with list of contents, and preceded by another sermon, usually counted as the first, and by the usual prologue or 'Epistola Æthelredi abbatis Rieuallis ad Gislebertum [Foliot] uenerabilem episcopum Londoniensem'. Through the loss of a gathering after fol. 122 all is gone after the words 'Usque ad Iazer peruenerunt' in the penultimate sermon.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="MS_Bodl_139-item2">
                     <locus from="123">(fol. 123)</locus>
                     <author key="person_39386818">Aelred of Rievaulx</author>
                     <title key="work_264">De spirituali amicitia</title>
                     <rubric>Explicit liber tertius domini Æ. abbatis de spirituali amicitia</rubric>
                     <note>The first part, to the words 'fruendum; per quem &amp; fruitur', is lost: one leaf is also lost after fol. 125.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="annotation">There are some marginal notes and scribblings.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
